properties.headline: Winter Storm Watch issued January 10 at 4:03AM CST until January 12 at 3:00AM CST by NWS Chicago IL
properties.description:
...Periods of Wintry Precipitation, Possibly Significant, Tonight
Through Saturday Night...

* WHAT...A mix of freezing rain and sleet is possible overnight,
especially north of a line from Mendota to Elgin. The light to
moderate mix is more likely across the area Saturday morning
into the afternoon, with a change to all snow, possibly heavy,
late Saturday afternoon and evening. Total ice accumulations of
one tenth to two tenths of an inch are possible very late
tonight into Saturday morning, with sleet accumulation also
possible. Total snow accumulations in excess of 3 inches are
also possible late Saturday afternoon and evening. Northeast
winds will gust as high as 40 mph overnight into Saturday.

* WHERE...DuPage, Kane, Kendall, and La Salle Counties.

* WHEN...Late tonight through Saturday night.

* IMPACTS...Power outages and tree damage are possible due to the
ice and windy conditions. Travel could be significantly impacted
across the area at times late tonight through Saturday evening.
properties.instruction: Monitor the latest forecasts for updates on this situation.

NWSheadline: WINTER STORM WATCH REMAINS IN EFFECT FROM LATE TONIGHT THROUGH LATE SATURDAY NIGHT
